==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stalk-eyed
<hw>Stalk"-eyed`</hw> <pr>(st⟦add⟧k"⟦imac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the eyes raised on a stalk, or peduncle;
-- opposed to <contr>sessile-eyed</contr>. Said especially of
podophthalmous crustaceans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stalk-eyed crustaceans</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<cd>See <er>Podophthalmia</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stalking-horse</ent>⟦br⟧
